31 // Adds Arm64-specific methods to convert InstructionOperands.
32 class Arm64OperandConverter final : public InstructionOperandConverter {
33  public:
34  Arm64OperandConverter(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
35  : InstructionOperandConverter(gen, instr) {}
36 
37  DoubleRegister InputFloat32Register(size_t index) {
38  return InputDoubleRegister(index).S();
39  }
40 
41  DoubleRegister InputFloat64Register(size_t index) {
42  return InputDoubleRegister(index);
43  }
44 
45  DoubleRegister InputSimd128Register(size_t index) {
46  return InputDoubleRegister(index).Q();
47  }
48 
49  CPURegister InputFloat32OrZeroRegister(size_t index) {
50  if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
51  DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int32_t>(InputFloat32(index)));
52  return wzr;
53  }
54  DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsFPRegister());
55  return InputDoubleRegister(index).S();
56  }
57 
58  DoubleRegister InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(size_t index) {
59  if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
60  DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int32_t>(InputFloat32(index)));
61  return fp_zero.S();
62  }
63  DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsFPRegister());
64  return InputDoubleRegister(index).S();
65  }
66 
67  CPURegister InputFloat64OrZeroRegister(size_t index) {
68  if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
69  DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int64_t>(InputDouble(index)));
70  return xzr;
71  }
72  DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsDoubleRegister());
73  return InputDoubleRegister(index);
74  }
75 
76  DoubleRegister InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(size_t index) {
77  if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
78  DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int64_t>(InputDouble(index)));
79  return fp_zero;
80  }
81  DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsDoubleRegister());
82  return InputDoubleRegister(index);
83  }
84 
85  size_t OutputCount() { return instr_->OutputCount(); }
86 
87  DoubleRegister OutputFloat32Register(size_t index = 0) {
88  return OutputDoubleRegister(index).S();
89  }
90 
91  DoubleRegister OutputFloat64Register(size_t index = 0) {
92  return OutputDoubleRegister(index);
93  }
94 
95  DoubleRegister OutputSimd128Register(size_t index = 0) {
96  return OutputDoubleRegister(index).Q();
97  }
98 
99  Register InputRegister32(size_t index) {
100  return ToRegister(instr_->InputAt(index)).W();
101  }
102 
103  Register InputOrZeroRegister32(size_t index) {
104  DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsRegister() ||
105  (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate() && (InputInt32(index) == 0)));
106  if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
107  return wzr;
108  }
109  return InputRegister32(index);
110  }
111 
112  Register InputRegister64(size_t index) { return InputRegister(index); }
113 
114  Register InputOrZeroRegister64(size_t index) {
115  DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsRegister() ||
116  (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate() && (InputInt64(index) == 0)));
117  if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
118  return xzr;
119  }
120  return InputRegister64(index);
121  }
122 
123  Operand InputOperand(size_t index) {
124  return ToOperand(instr_->InputAt(index));
125  }
126 
127  Operand InputOperand64(size_t index) { return InputOperand(index); }
128 
129  Operand InputOperand32(size_t index) {
130  return ToOperand32(instr_->InputAt(index));
131  }
132 
133  Register OutputRegister64(size_t index = 0) { return OutputRegister(index); }
134 
135  Register OutputRegister32(size_t index = 0) {
136  return OutputRegister(index).W();
137  }
138 
139  Register TempRegister32(size_t index) {
140  return ToRegister(instr_->TempAt(index)).W();
141  }
142 
143  Operand InputOperand2_32(size_t index) {
144  switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
145  case kMode_None:
146  return InputOperand32(index);
147  case kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I:
148  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), LSL, InputInt5(index + 1));
149  case kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I:
150  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), LSR, InputInt5(index + 1));
151  case kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I:
152  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), ASR, InputInt5(index + 1));
153  case kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I:
154  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), ROR, InputInt5(index + 1));
155  case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB:
156  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), UXTB);
157  case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH:
158  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), UXTH);
159  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB:
160  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), SXTB);
161  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH:
162  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), SXTH);
163  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW:
164  return Operand(InputRegister32(index), SXTW);
165  case kMode_MRI:
166  case kMode_MRR:
167  case kMode_Root:
168  break;
169  }
170  UNREACHABLE();
171  }
172 
173  Operand InputOperand2_64(size_t index) {
174  switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
175  case kMode_None:
176  return InputOperand64(index);
177  case kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I:
178  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), LSL, InputInt6(index + 1));
179  case kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I:
180  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), LSR, InputInt6(index + 1));
181  case kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I:
182  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), ASR, InputInt6(index + 1));
183  case kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I:
184  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), ROR, InputInt6(index + 1));
185  case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB:
186  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), UXTB);
187  case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH:
188  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), UXTH);
189  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB:
190  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), SXTB);
191  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH:
192  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), SXTH);
193  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW:
194  return Operand(InputRegister64(index), SXTW);
195  case kMode_MRI:
196  case kMode_MRR:
197  case kMode_Root:
198  break;
199  }
200  UNREACHABLE();
201  }
202 
203  MemOperand MemoryOperand(size_t index = 0) {
204  switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
205  case kMode_None:
206  case kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I:
207  case kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I:
208  case kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I:
209  case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB:
210  case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH:
211  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB:
212  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH:
213  case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW:
214  break;
215  case kMode_Root:
216  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, InputInt64(index));
217  case kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I:
218  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1),
219  LSL, InputInt32(index + 2));
220  case kMode_MRI:
221  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputInt32(index + 1));
222  case kMode_MRR:
223  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1));
224  }
225  UNREACHABLE();
226  }
227 
228  Operand ToOperand(InstructionOperand* op) {
229  if (op->IsRegister()) {
230  return Operand(ToRegister(op));
231  }
232  return ToImmediate(op);
233  }
234 
235  Operand ToOperand32(InstructionOperand* op) {
236  if (op->IsRegister()) {
237  return Operand(ToRegister(op).W());
238  }
239  return ToImmediate(op);
240  }
241 
242  Operand ToImmediate(InstructionOperand* operand) {
243  Constant constant = ToConstant(operand);
244  switch (constant.type()) {
245  case Constant::kInt32:
246  return Operand(constant.ToInt32(), constant.rmode());
247  case Constant::kInt64:
248  return Operand(constant.ToInt64(), constant.rmode());
249  case Constant::kFloat32:
250  return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat32());
251  case Constant::kFloat64:
252  return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat64().value());
253  case Constant::kExternalReference:
254  return Operand(constant.ToExternalReference());
255  case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject: {
256  RootIndex root_index;
257  if (gen_->isolate()->roots_table().IsRootHandle(constant.ToHeapObject(),
258  &root_index)) {
259  CHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
260  CHECK(V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL || !gen_->isolate()->bootstrapper());
261  Tagged_t ptr =
262  MacroAssemblerBase::ReadOnlyRootPtr(root_index, gen_->isolate());
263  CHECK(Assembler::IsImmAddSub(ptr));
264  return Immediate(ptr);
265  }
266 
267  return Operand(constant.ToHeapObject());
268  }
269  case Constant::kHeapObject:
270  return Operand(constant.ToHeapObject());
271  case Constant::kRpoNumber:
272  UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(dcarney): RPO immediates on arm64.
273  }
274  UNREACHABLE();
275  }
276 
277  MemOperand ToMemOperand(InstructionOperand* op, MacroAssembler* masm) const {
278  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(op);
279  DCHECK(op->IsStackSlot() || op->IsFPStackSlot());
280  return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index(), masm);
281  }
282 
283  MemOperand SlotToMemOperand(int slot, MacroAssembler* masm) const {
284  FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(slot);
285  if (offset.from_frame_pointer()) {
286  int from_sp = offset.offset() + frame_access_state()->GetSPToFPOffset();
287  // Convert FP-offsets to SP-offsets if it results in better code.
288  if (!frame_access_state()->frame()->invalidates_sp() &&
289  (Assembler::IsImmLSUnscaled(from_sp) ||
290  Assembler::IsImmLSScaled(from_sp, 3))) {
291  offset = FrameOffset::FromStackPointer(from_sp);
292  }
293  }
294  // Access below the stack pointer is not expected in arm64 and is actively
295  // prevented at run time in the simulator.
296  DCHECK_IMPLIES(offset.from_stack_pointer(), offset.offset() >= 0);
297  return MemOperand(offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp, offset.offset());
298  }
299 };

303 class OutOfLineRecordWrite final : public OutOfLineCode {
304  public:
305  OutOfLineRecordWrite(
306  CodeGenerator* gen, Register object, Operand offset, Register value,
307  RecordWriteMode mode, StubCallMode stub_mode,
308  UnwindingInfoWriter* unwinding_info_writer,
309  IndirectPointerTag indirect_pointer_tag = kIndirectPointerNullTag)
310  : OutOfLineCode(gen),
311  object_(object),
312  offset_(offset),
313  value_(value),
314  mode_(mode),
315 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
316  stub_mode_(stub_mode),
317 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
318  must_save_lr_(!gen->frame_access_state()->has_frame()),
319  unwinding_info_writer_(unwinding_info_writer),
320  zone_(gen->zone()),
321  indirect_pointer_tag_(indirect_pointer_tag) {
322  }
323 
324  void Generate() final {
325  // When storing an indirect pointer, the value will always be a
326  // full/decompressed pointer.
327  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL &&
328  mode_ != RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
329  __ DecompressTagged(value_, value_);
330  }
331 
332  // No need to check value page flags with the indirect pointer write barrier
333  // because the value is always an ExposedTrustedObject.
334  if (mode_ != RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
335  __ CheckPageFlag(value_, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
336  eq, exit());
337  }
338 
339  SaveFPRegsMode const save_fp_mode = frame()->DidAllocateDoubleRegisters()
340  ? SaveFPRegsMode::kSave
341  : SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore;
342  if (must_save_lr_) {
343  // We need to save and restore lr if the frame was elided.
344  __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, padreg);
345  unwinding_info_writer_->MarkLinkRegisterOnTopOfStack(__ pc_offset(), sp);
346  }
347  if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsEphemeronKey) {
348  __ CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode);
349  } else if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
350  // We must have a valid indirect pointer tag here. Otherwise, we risk not
351  // invoking the correct write barrier, which may lead to subtle issues.
352  CHECK(IsValidIndirectPointerTag(indirect_pointer_tag_));
353  __ CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode,
354  indirect_pointer_tag_);
355 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
356  } else if (stub_mode_ == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
357  // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
358  // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched when the code
359  // is added to the native module and copied into wasm code space.
360  __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode,
361  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
362 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
363  } else {
364  __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode);
365  }
366  if (must_save_lr_) {
367  __ Pop<MacroAssembler::kAuthLR>(padreg, lr);
368  unwinding_info_writer_->MarkPopLinkRegisterFromTopOfStack(__ pc_offset());
369  }
370  }
371 
372  private:
373  Register const object_;
374  Operand const offset_;
375  Register const value_;
376  RecordWriteMode const mode_;
377 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
378  StubCallMode const stub_mode_;
379 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
380  bool must_save_lr_;
381  UnwindingInfoWriter* const unwinding_info_writer_;
382  Zone* zone_;
383  IndirectPointerTag indirect_pointer_tag_;
384 };
385 
386 Condition FlagsConditionToCondition(FlagsCondition condition) {
387  switch (condition) {
388  case kEqual:
389  return eq;
390  case kNotEqual:
391  return ne;
392  case kSignedLessThan:
393  return lt;
394  case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
395  return ge;
396  case kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
397  return le;
398  case kSignedGreaterThan:
399  return gt;
400  case kUnsignedLessThan:
401  return lo;
402  case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
403  return hs;
404  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
405  return ls;
406  case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
407  return hi;
408  case kFloatLessThanOrUnordered:
409  return lt;
410  case kFloatGreaterThanOrEqual:
411  return ge;
412  case kFloatLessThanOrEqual:
413  return ls;
414  case kFloatGreaterThanOrUnordered:
415  return hi;
416  case kFloatLessThan:
417  return lo;
418  case kFloatGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered:
419  return hs;
420  case kFloatLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered:
421  return le;
422  case kFloatGreaterThan:
423  return gt;
424  case kOverflow:
425  return vs;
426  case kNotOverflow:
427  return vc;
428  case kUnorderedEqual:
429  case kUnorderedNotEqual:
430  case kIsNaN:
431  case kIsNotNaN:
432  break;
433  case kPositiveOrZero:
434  return pl;
435  case kNegative:
436  return mi;
437  }
438  UNREACHABLE();
439 }

442 class WasmOutOfLineTrap : public OutOfLineCode {
443  public:
444  WasmOutOfLineTrap(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
445  : OutOfLineCode(gen), gen_(gen), instr_(instr) {}
446  void Generate() override {
447  Arm64OperandConverter i(gen_, instr_);
448  TrapId trap_id =
449  static_cast<TrapId>(i.InputInt32(instr_->InputCount() - 1));
450  GenerateCallToTrap(trap_id);
451  }
452 
453  protected:
454  CodeGenerator* gen_;
455 
456  void GenerateWithTrapId(TrapId trap_id) { GenerateCallToTrap(trap_id); }
457 
458  private:
459  void GenerateCallToTrap(TrapId trap_id) {
460  gen_->AssembleSourcePosition(instr_);
461  __ Call(static_cast<Address>(trap_id), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
462  ReferenceMap* reference_map = gen_->zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(gen_->zone());
463  gen_->RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
464  __ AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromWasmTrap);
465  }
466 
467  Instruction* instr_;
468 };

470 void RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(Zone* zone, CodeGenerator* codegen,
471  InstructionCode opcode, Instruction* instr,
472  int pc) {
473  const MemoryAccessMode access_mode = AccessModeField::decode(opcode);
474  if (access_mode == kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds ||
475  access_mode == kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference) {
476  codegen->RecordProtectedInstruction(pc);
477  }
478 }
479 #else
480 void RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(Zone* zone, CodeGenerator* codegen,
481  InstructionCode opcode, Instruction* instr,
482  int pc) {
483  DCHECK_EQ(kMemoryAccessDirect, AccessModeField::decode(opcode));
484 }

487 // Handles unary ops that work for float (scalar), double (scalar), or NEON.
488 template <typename Fn>
489 void EmitFpOrNeonUnop(MacroAssembler* masm, Fn fn, Instruction* instr,
490  Arm64OperandConverter i, VectorFormat scalar,
491  VectorFormat vector) {
492  VectorFormat f = instr->InputAt(0)->IsSimd128Register() ? vector : scalar;
493 
494  VRegister output = VRegister::Create(i.OutputDoubleRegister().code(), f);
495  VRegister input = VRegister::Create(i.InputDoubleRegister(0).code(), f);
496  (masm->*fn)(output, input);
497 }

501 #define ASSEMBLE_SHIFT(asm_instr, width) \
502  do { \
503  if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsRegister()) { \
504  __ asm_instr(i.OutputRegister##width(), i.InputRegister##width(0), \
505  i.InputRegister##width(1)); \
506  } else { \
507  uint32_t imm = \
508  static_cast<uint32_t>(i.InputOperand##width(1).ImmediateValue()); \
509  __ asm_instr(i.OutputRegister##width(), i.InputRegister##width(0), \
510  imm % (width)); \
511  } \
512  } while (0)
513 
514 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_LOAD_INTEGER(asm_instr, reg) \
515  do { \
516  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
517  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
518  __ asm_instr(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
519  } while (0)
520 
521 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_STORE_INTEGER(asm_instr, reg) \
522  do { \
523  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
524  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
525  __ asm_instr(i.Input##reg(2), i.TempRegister(0)); \
526  } while (0)
527 
528 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(suffix, reg) \
529  do { \
530  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
531  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
532  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
533  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
534  __ Swpal##suffix(i.Input##reg(2), i.Output##reg(), \
535  MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
536  } else { \
537  Label exchange; \
538  __ Bind(&exchange); \
539  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
540  __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
541  __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(1), i.Input##reg(2), \
542  i.TempRegister(0)); \
543  __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(1), &exchange); \
544  } \
545  } while (0)
546 
547 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(suffix, ext, reg) \
548  do { \
549  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
550  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
551  DCHECK_EQ(i.OutputRegister(), i.InputRegister(2)); \
552  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
553  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
554  __ Casal##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.Input##reg(3), \
555  MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
556  } else { \
557  Label compareExchange; \
558  Label exit; \
559  __ Bind(&compareExchange); \
560  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
561  __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
562  __ Cmp(i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2), ext)); \
563  __ B(ne, &exit); \
564  __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(1), i.Input##reg(3), \
565  i.TempRegister(0)); \
566  __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(1), &compareExchange); \
567  __ Bind(&exit); \
568  } \
569  } while (0)
570 
571 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_SUB(suffix, reg) \
572  do { \
573  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
574  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
575  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
576  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
577  Register scratch = temps.AcquireSameSizeAs(i.Input##reg(2)); \
578  __ Neg(scratch, i.Input##reg(2)); \
579  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
580  __ Ldaddal##suffix(scratch, i.Output##reg(), \
581  MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
582  } else { \
583  Label binop; \
584  __ Bind(&binop); \
585  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
586  __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
587  __ Sub(i.Temp##reg(1), i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2))); \
588  __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(2), i.Temp##reg(1), \
589  i.TempRegister(0)); \
590  __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(2), &binop); \
591  } \
592  } while (0)
593 
594 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_AND(suffix, reg) \
595  do { \
596  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
597  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
598  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
599  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
600  Register scratch = temps.AcquireSameSizeAs(i.Input##reg(2)); \
601  __ Mvn(scratch, i.Input##reg(2)); \
602  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
603  __ Ldclral##suffix(scratch, i.Output##reg(), \
604  MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
605  } else { \
606  Label binop; \
607  __ Bind(&binop); \
608  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
609  __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
610  __ And(i.Temp##reg(1), i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2))); \
611  __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(2), i.Temp##reg(1), \
612  i.TempRegister(0)); \
613  __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(2), &binop); \
614  } \
615  } while (0)
616 
617 #define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(suffix, bin_instr, lse_instr, reg) \
618  do { \
619  __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
620  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
621  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
622  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
623  __ lse_instr##suffix(i.Input##reg(2), i.Output##reg(), \
624  MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
625  } else { \
626  Label binop; \
627  __ Bind(&binop); \
628  RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
629  __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
630  __ bin_instr(i.Temp##reg(1), i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2))); \
631  __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(2), i.Temp##reg(1), \
632  i.TempRegister(0)); \
633  __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(2), &binop); \
634  } \
635  } while (0)
636 
637 #define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_BINOP(name) \
638  do { \
639  FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
640  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 2); \
641  } while (0)
642 
643 #define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(name) \
644  do { \
645  FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
646  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 1); \
647  } while (0)
648 
649 // If shift value is an immediate, we can call asm_imm, taking the shift value
650 // modulo 2^width. Otherwise, emit code to perform the modulus operation, and
651 // call asm_shl.
652 #define ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_LEFT(asm_imm, width, format, asm_shl, gp) \
653  do { \
654  if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsImmediate()) { \
655  __ asm_imm(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
656  i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), i.InputInt##width(1)); \
657  } else { \
658  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
659  VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireQ(); \
660  Register shift = temps.Acquire##gp(); \
661  constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1; \
662  __ And(shift, i.InputRegister32(1), mask); \
663  __ Dup(tmp.format(), shift); \
664  __ asm_shl(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
665  i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), tmp.format()); \
666  } \
667  } while (0)
668 
669 // If shift value is an immediate, we can call asm_imm, taking the shift value
670 // modulo 2^width. Otherwise, emit code to perform the modulus operation, and
671 // call asm_shl, passing in the negative shift value (treated as right shift).
672 #define ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_RIGHT(asm_imm, width, format, asm_shl, gp) \
673  do { \
674  if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsImmediate()) { \
675  __ asm_imm(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
676  i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), i.InputInt##width(1)); \
677  } else { \
678  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
679  VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireQ(); \
680  Register shift = temps.Acquire##gp(); \
681  constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1; \
682  __ And(shift, i.InputRegister32(1), mask); \
683  __ Dup(tmp.format(), shift); \
684  __ Neg(tmp.format(), tmp.format()); \
685  __ asm_shl(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
686  i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), tmp.format()); \
687  } \
688  } while (0)

706 void AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(MacroAssembler* masm,
707  FrameAccessState* state,
708  int new_slot_above_sp,
709  bool allow_shrinkage = true) {
710  int current_sp_offset = state->GetSPToFPSlotCount() +
711  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountAboveFp;
712  int stack_slot_delta = new_slot_above_sp - current_sp_offset;
713  DCHECK_EQ(stack_slot_delta % 2, 0);
714  if (stack_slot_delta > 0) {
715  masm->Claim(stack_slot_delta);
716  state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
717  } else if (allow_shrinkage && stack_slot_delta < 0) {
718  masm->Drop(-stack_slot_delta);
719  state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
720  }
721 }

754 // Check that {kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister} is correct.
755 void CodeGenerator::AssembleDispatchHandleRegisterCheck() {
756  DCHECK(linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->IsJSFunctionCall());
757 
758  if (!V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL) return;
759 
760  // We currently don't check this for JS builtins as those are sometimes

785 int32_t GetLaneMask(int32_t lane_count) { return lane_count * 2 - 1; }

787 void Shuffle1Helper(MacroAssembler* masm, Arm64OperandConverter i,
788  VectorFormat f) {
789  VRegister dst = VRegister::Create(i.OutputSimd128Register().code(), f);
790  VRegister src0 = VRegister::Create(i.InputSimd128Register(0).code(), f);
791  VRegister src1 = VRegister::Create(i.InputSimd128Register(1).code(), f);
792 
793  int32_t shuffle = i.InputInt32(2);
794  int32_t lane_count = LaneCountFromFormat(f);
795  int32_t max_src0_lane = lane_count - 1;
796  int32_t lane_mask = GetLaneMask(lane_count);
797 
798  int lane = shuffle & lane_mask;
799  VRegister src = (lane > max_src0_lane) ? src1 : src0;
800  lane &= max_src0_lane;
801  masm->Dup(dst, src, lane);
802 }
803 
804 void Shuffle2Helper(MacroAssembler* masm, Arm64OperandConverter i,
805  VectorFormat f) {
806  VRegister dst = VRegister::Create(i.OutputSimd128Register().code(), f);
807  VRegister src0 = VRegister::Create(i.InputSimd128Register(0).code(), f);
808  VRegister src1 = VRegister::Create(i.InputSimd128Register(1).code(), f);
809  // Check for in-place shuffles, as we may need to use a temporary register
810  // to avoid overwriting an input.
811  if (dst == src0 || dst == src1) {
812  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm);
813  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(f);
814  if (dst == src0) {
815  masm->Mov(temp, src0);
816  src0 = temp;
817  } else if (dst == src1) {
818  masm->Mov(temp, src1);
819  src1 = temp;
820  }
821  }
822  int32_t shuffle = i.InputInt32(2);
823  int32_t lane_count = LaneCountFromFormat(f);
824  int32_t max_src0_lane = lane_count - 1;
825  int32_t lane_mask = GetLaneMask(lane_count);
826 
827  // Perform shuffle as a vmov per lane.
828  for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
829  VRegister src = src0;
830  int lane = shuffle & lane_mask;
831  if (lane > max_src0_lane) {
832  src = src1;
833  lane &= max_src0_lane;
834  }
835  masm->Mov(dst, i, src, lane);
836  shuffle >>= 8;
837  }
838 }
839 
840 void Shuffle4Helper(MacroAssembler* masm, Arm64OperandConverter i,
841  VectorFormat f) {
842  VRegister dst = VRegister::Create(i.OutputSimd128Register().code(), f);
843  VRegister src0 = VRegister::Create(i.InputSimd128Register(0).code(), f);
844  VRegister src1 = VRegister::Create(i.InputSimd128Register(1).code(), f);
845  // Check for in-place shuffles, as we may need to use a temporary register
846  // to avoid overwriting an input.
847  if (dst == src0 || dst == src1) {
848  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm);
849  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(f);
850  if (dst == src0) {
851  masm->Mov(temp, src0);
852  src0 = temp;
853  } else if (dst == src1) {
854  masm->Mov(temp, src1);
855  src1 = temp;
856  }
857  }
858  int32_t shuffle = i.InputInt32(2);
859  int32_t lane_count = LaneCountFromFormat(f);
860  int32_t max_src0_lane = lane_count - 1;
861  int32_t lane_mask = GetLaneMask(lane_count);
862 
863  DCHECK_EQ(f, kFormat4S);
864  // Check whether we can reduce the number of vmovs by performing a dup
865  // first. So, for [1, 1, 2, 1] we can dup lane zero and then perform
866  // a single lane move for lane two.
867  const std::array<int, 4> input_lanes{
868  shuffle & lane_mask, shuffle >> 8 & lane_mask, shuffle >> 16 & lane_mask,
869  shuffle >> 24 & lane_mask};
870  std::array<int, 8> lane_counts = {0};
871  for (int lane : input_lanes) {
872  ++lane_counts[lane];
873  }
874 
875  // Find first duplicate lane, if any, and insert dup.
876  int duplicate_lane = -1;
877  for (size_t lane = 0; lane < lane_counts.size(); ++lane) {
878  if (lane_counts[lane] > 1) {
879  duplicate_lane = static_cast<int>(lane);
880  if (duplicate_lane > max_src0_lane) {
881  masm->Dup(dst, src1, duplicate_lane & max_src0_lane);
882  } else {
883  masm->Dup(dst, src0, duplicate_lane);
884  }
885  break;
886  }
887  }
888 
889  // Perform shuffle as a vmov per lane.
890  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
891  int lane = shuffle & lane_mask;
892  shuffle >>= 8;
893  if (lane == duplicate_lane) continue;
894  VRegister src = src0;
895  if (lane > max_src0_lane) {
896  src = src1;
897  lane &= max_src0_lane;
898  }
899  masm->Mov(dst, i, src, lane);
900  }
901 }

903 // Assembles an instruction after register allocation, producing machine code.
904 CodeGenerator::CodeGenResult CodeGenerator::AssembleArchInstruction(
905  Instruction* instr) {
906  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
907  InstructionCode opcode = instr->opcode();
908  ArchOpcode arch_opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(opcode);
909  switch (arch_opcode) {
910  case kArchCallCodeObject: {
911  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
912  __ Call(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
913  } else {
914  Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
915  CodeEntrypointTag tag =
916  i.InputCodeEntrypointTag(instr->CodeEnrypointTagInputIndex());
917  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
918  instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
919  reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
920  __ CallCodeObject(reg, tag);
921  }
922  RecordCallPosition(instr);
923  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
924  break;
925  }
926  case kArchCallBuiltinPointer: {
927  DCHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
928  Register builtin_index = i.InputRegister(0);
929  Register target =
930  instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister)
931  ? kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister
932  : builtin_index;
933  __ CallBuiltinByIndex(builtin_index, target);
934  RecordCallPosition(instr);
935  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
936  break;
937  }
938 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
939  case kArchCallWasmFunction:
940  case kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect: {
941  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
942  DCHECK_EQ(arch_opcode, kArchCallWasmFunction);
943  Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
944  Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
945  __ Call(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
946  } else if (arch_opcode == kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect) {
947  __ CallWasmCodePointer(
948  i.InputRegister(0),
949  i.InputInt64(instr->WasmSignatureHashInputIndex()));
950  } else {
951  __ Call(i.InputRegister(0));
952  }
953  RecordCallPosition(instr);
954  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
955  break;
956  }
957  case kArchTailCallWasm:
958  case kArchTailCallWasmIndirect: {
959  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
960  DCHECK_EQ(arch_opcode, kArchTailCallWasm);
961  Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
962  Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
963  __ Jump(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
964  } else {
965  Register target = i.InputRegister(0);
966  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
967  temps.Exclude(x17);
968  __ Mov(x17, target);
969  if (arch_opcode == kArchTailCallWasmIndirect) {
970  __ CallWasmCodePointer(
971  x17, i.InputInt64(instr->WasmSignatureHashInputIndex()),
972  CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
973  } else {
974  __ Jump(x17);
975  }
976  }
977  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
978  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
979  frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
980  break;
981  }
982 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
983  case kArchTailCallCodeObject: {
984  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
985  __ Jump(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
986  } else {
987  Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
988  CodeEntrypointTag tag =
989  i.InputCodeEntrypointTag(instr->CodeEnrypointTagInputIndex());
990  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
991  instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
992  reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
993  __ JumpCodeObject(reg, tag);
994  }
995  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
996  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
997  frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
998  break;
999  }
1000  case kArchTailCallAddress: {
1001  CHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
1002  Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
1003  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1004  instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
1005  reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1006  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
1007  temps.Exclude(x17);
1008  __ Mov(x17, reg);
1009  __ Jump(x17);
1010  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
1011  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1012  frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
1013  break;
1014  }
1015  case kArchCallJSFunction: {
1016  Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
1017  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1018  // Check the function's context matches the context argument.
1019  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
1020  Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
1021  __ LoadTaggedField(temp,
1022  FieldMemOperand(func, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
1023  __ cmp(cp, temp);
1024  __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionContext);
1025  }
1026  uint32_t num_arguments =
1027  i.InputUint32(instr->JSCallArgumentCountInputIndex());
1028  __ CallJSFunction(func, num_arguments);
1029  RecordCallPosition(instr);
1030  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1031  break;
1032  }
1033  case kArchPrepareCallCFunction:
1034  // We don't need kArchPrepareCallCFunction on arm64 as the instruction
1035  // selector has already performed a Claim to reserve space on the stack.
1036  // Frame alignment is always 16 bytes, and the stack pointer is already
1037  // 16-byte aligned, therefore we do not need to align the stack pointer
1038  // by an unknown value, and it is safe to continue accessing the frame
1039  // via the stack pointer.
1040  UNREACHABLE();
1041  case kArchSaveCallerRegisters: {
1042  fp_mode_ =
1043  static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode()));
1044  DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
1045  fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
1046  // kReturnRegister0 should have been saved before entering the stub.
1047  int bytes = __ PushCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
1048  DCHECK(IsAligned(bytes, kSystemPointerSize));
1049  DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
1050  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
1051  DCHECK(!caller_registers_saved_);
1052  caller_registers_saved_ = true;
1053  break;
1054  }
1055  case kArchRestoreCallerRegisters: {
1056  DCHECK(fp_mode_ ==
1057  static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode())));
1058  DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
1059  fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
1060  // Don't overwrite the returned value.
1061  int bytes = __ PopCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
1062  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-(bytes / kSystemPointerSize));
1063  DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
1064  DCHECK(caller_registers_saved_);
1065  caller_registers_saved_ = false;
1066  break;
1067  }
1068  case kArchPrepareTailCall:
1069  AssemblePrepareTailCall();
1070  break;
1071  case kArchCallCFunction: {
1072  uint32_t param_counts = i.InputUint32(instr->InputCount() - 1);
1073  int const num_gp_parameters = ParamField::decode(param_counts);
1074  int const num_fp_parameters = FPParamField::decode(param_counts);
1075  Label return_location;
1076  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes;
1077 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1078  if (linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
1079  // Put the return address in a stack slot.
1080  __ StoreReturnAddressInWasmExitFrame(&return_location);
1081  set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo;
1082  }
1083 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1084  int pc_offset;
1085  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
1086  ExternalReference ref = i.InputExternalReference(0);
1087  pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(ref, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
1088  set_isolate_data_slots, &return_location);
1089  } else {
1090  Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
1091  pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(func, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
1092  set_isolate_data_slots, &return_location);
1093  }
1094  RecordSafepoint(instr->reference_map(), pc_offset);
1095 
1096  if (instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kHasExceptionHandler)) {
1097  handlers_.push_back({nullptr, pc_offset});
1098  }
1099  if (instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState)) {
1100  RecordDeoptInfo(instr, pc_offset);
1101  }
1102 
1103  frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
1104  // Ideally, we should decrement SP delta to match the change of stack
1105  // pointer in CallCFunction. However, for certain architectures (e.g.
1106  // ARM), there may be more strict alignment requirement, causing old SP
1107  // to be saved on the stack. In those cases, we can not calculate the SP
1108  // delta statically.
1109  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1110  if (caller_registers_saved_) {
1111  // Need to re-sync SP delta introduced in kArchSaveCallerRegisters.
1112  // Here, we assume the sequence to be:
1113  // kArchSaveCallerRegisters;
1114  // kArchCallCFunction;
1115  // kArchRestoreCallerRegisters;
1116  int bytes =
1117  __ RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
1118  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
1119  }
1120  break;
1121  }
1122  case kArchJmp:
1123  AssembleArchJump(i.InputRpo(0));
1124  break;
1125  case kArchTableSwitch:
1126  AssembleArchTableSwitch(instr);
1127  break;
1128  case kArchBinarySearchSwitch:
1129  AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitch(instr);
1130  break;
1131  case kArchAbortCSADcheck:

2915  case kArm64I64x2Mul: {
2916  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
2917  VRegister dst = i.OutputSimd128Register();
2918  VRegister src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(0);
2919  VRegister src2 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
2920  VRegister tmp1 = scope.AcquireSameSizeAs(dst);
2921  VRegister tmp2 = scope.AcquireSameSizeAs(dst);
2922  VRegister tmp3 = i.ToSimd128Register(instr->TempAt(0));
2923 
2924  // This 2x64-bit multiplication is performed with several 32-bit
2925  // multiplications.
2926 
2927  // 64-bit numbers x and y, can be represented as:
2928  // x = a + 2^32(b)
2929  // y = c + 2^32(d)
2930 
2931  // A 64-bit multiplication is:
2932  // x * y = ac + 2^32(ad + bc) + 2^64(bd)
2933  // note: `2^64(bd)` can be ignored, the value is too large to fit in
2934  // 64-bits.
2935 
2936  // This sequence implements a 2x64bit multiply, where the registers
2937  // `src1` and `src2` are split up into 32-bit components:
2938  // src1 = |d|c|b|a|
2939  // src2 = |h|g|f|e|
2940  //
2941  // src1 * src2 = |cg + 2^32(ch + dg)|ae + 2^32(af + be)|
2942 
2943  // Reverse the 32-bit elements in the 64-bit words.
2944  // tmp2 = |g|h|e|f|
2945  __ Rev64(tmp2.V4S(), src2.V4S());
2946 
2947  // Calculate the high half components.
2948  // tmp2 = |dg|ch|be|af|
2949  __ Mul(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), src1.V4S());
2950 
2951  // Extract the low half components of src1.
2952  // tmp1 = |c|a|
2953  __ Xtn(tmp1.V2S(), src1.V2D());
2954 
2955  // Sum the respective high half components.
2956  // tmp2 = |dg+ch|be+af||dg+ch|be+af|
2957  __ Addp(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S());
2958 
2959  // Extract the low half components of src2.
2960  // tmp3 = |g|e|
2961  __ Xtn(tmp3.V2S(), src2.V2D());
2962 
2963  // Shift the high half components, into the high half.
2964  // dst = |dg+ch << 32|be+af << 32|
2965  __ Shll(dst.V2D(), tmp2.V2S(), 32);
2966 
2967  // Multiply the low components together, and accumulate with the high
2968  // half.
2969  // dst = |dst[1] + cg|dst[0] + ae|
2970  __ Umlal(dst.V2D(), tmp3.V2S(), tmp1.V2S());
2971 
2972  break;
2973  }

3488 // Assemble branches after this instruction.
3489 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBranch(Instruction* instr, BranchInfo* branch) {
3490  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3491  Label* tlabel = branch->true_label;
3492  Label* flabel = branch->false_label;
3493  FlagsCondition condition = branch->condition;
3494  ArchOpcode opcode = instr->arch_opcode();
3495 
3496  if (opcode == kArm64CompareAndBranch32) {
3497  switch (condition) {
3498  case kEqual:
3499  __ Cbz(i.InputRegister32(0), tlabel);
3500  break;
3501  case kNotEqual:
3502  __ Cbnz(i.InputRegister32(0), tlabel);
3503  break;
3504  default:
3505  UNREACHABLE();
3506  }
3507  } else if (opcode == kArm64CompareAndBranch) {
3508  switch (condition) {
3509  case kEqual:
3510  __ Cbz(i.InputRegister64(0), tlabel);
3511  break;
3512  case kNotEqual:
3513  __ Cbnz(i.InputRegister64(0), tlabel);
3514  break;
3515  default:
3516  UNREACHABLE();
3517  }
3518  } else if (opcode == kArm64TestAndBranch32) {
3519  switch (condition) {
3520  case kEqual:
3521  __ Tbz(i.InputRegister32(0), i.InputInt5(1), tlabel);
3522  break;
3523  case kNotEqual:
3524  __ Tbnz(i.InputRegister32(0), i.InputInt5(1), tlabel);
3525  break;
3526  default:
3527  UNREACHABLE();
3528  }
3529  } else if (opcode == kArm64TestAndBranch) {
3530  switch (condition) {
3531  case kEqual:
3532  __ Tbz(i.InputRegister64(0), i.InputInt6(1), tlabel);
3533  break;
3534  case kNotEqual:
3535  __ Tbnz(i.InputRegister64(0), i.InputInt6(1), tlabel);
3536  break;
3537  default:
3538  UNREACHABLE();
3539  }
3540  } else {
3541  Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3542  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(HBC) && branch->hinted) {
3543  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), HBC);
3544  __ Bc(cc, tlabel);
3545  } else {
3546  __ B(cc, tlabel);
3547  }
3548  }
3549  if (!branch->fallthru) __ B(flabel); // no fallthru to flabel.
3550 }
3551 
3552 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchDeoptBranch(Instruction* instr,
3553  BranchInfo* branch) {
3554  AssembleArchBranch(instr, branch);
3555 }

3564  FlagsCondition condition) {
3565  auto ool = zone()->New<WasmOutOfLineTrap>(this, instr);
3566  Label* tlabel = ool->entry();
3567  Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3568  // Assume traps aren't taken, so they're consistent.
3569  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(HBC)) {
3570  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), HBC);
3571  __ Bc(cc, tlabel);
3572  } else {
3573  __ B(cc, tlabel);
3574  }

3578 // Assemble boolean materializations after this instruction.
3579 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBoolean(Instruction* instr,
3580  FlagsCondition condition) {
3581  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3582 
3583  // Materialize a full 64-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3584  // last output of the instruction.
3585  DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3586  Register reg = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3587  Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3588  __ Cset(reg, cc);
3589 }
3590 
3591 // Mnemonic Meaning (INT) Meaning (FP) Condition flags
3592 // EQ Equal Equal Z == 1
3593 // NE Not equal Not equal or unordered Z == 0
3594 // CS or HS Carry set >= or unordered C == 1
3595 // CC or LO Carry clear < C == 0
3596 // MI Minus, negative < N == 1
3597 // PL Plus, positive or zero >= or unordered N == 0
3598 // VS Overflow Unordered V == 1
3599 // VC No overflow Ordered V == 0
3600 // HI Unsigned > > or unordered C ==1 && Z == 0
3601 // LS Unsigned <= < or equal !(C ==1 && Z ==0)
3602 // GE Signed >= > or equal N == V
3603 // LT Signed < < or unordered N! = V
3604 // GT Signed >= > Z == 0 && N == V
3605 // LE Signed <= <= or unordered !(Z == 0 && N == V)
3606 // AL Always Always Any
3607 // NV Always Always Any
3608 
3609 // Given condition, return a value for nzcv which represents it. This is used
3610 // for the default condition for ccmp.
3611 inline StatusFlags ConditionToDefaultFlags(Condition condition) {
3612  switch (condition) {
3613  default:
3614  UNREACHABLE();
3615  case eq:
3616  return ZFlag; // Z == 1
3617  case ne:
3618  return NoFlag; // Z == 0
3619  case hs:
3620  return CFlag; // C == 1
3621  case lo:
3622  return NoFlag; // C == 0
3623  case mi:
3624  return NFlag; // N == 1
3625  case pl:
3626  return NoFlag; // N == 0
3627  case vs:
3628  return VFlag; // V == 1
3629  case vc:
3630  return NoFlag; // V == 0
3631  case hi:
3632  return CFlag; // C == 1 && Z == 0
3633  case ls:
3634  return NoFlag; // C == 0 || Z == 1
3635  case ge:
3636  return NoFlag; // N == V
3637  case lt:
3638  return NFlag; // N != V
3639  case gt:
3640  return NoFlag; // Z == 0 && N == V
3641  case le:
3642  return ZFlag; // Z == 1 || N != V
3643  }
3644 }

3646 void AssembleConditionalCompareChain(Instruction* instr, int64_t num_ccmps,
3647  size_t ccmp_base_index,
3648  CodeGenerator* gen) {
3649  Arm64OperandConverter i(gen, instr);
3650  // The first two, or three operands are the compare that begins the chain.
3651  // These operands are used when the first compare, the one with the
3652  // continuation attached, is generated.
3653  // Then, each five provide:
3654  // - cmp opcode
3655  // - compare lhs
3656  // - compare rhs
3657  // - default flags
3658  // - user condition
3659  for (unsigned n = 0; n < num_ccmps; ++n) {
3660  size_t opcode_index = ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfOpcode;
3661  size_t compare_lhs_index = ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfLhs;
3662  size_t compare_rhs_index = ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfRhs;
3663  size_t default_condition_index =
3664  ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfDefaultFlags;
3665  size_t compare_condition_index =
3666  ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfCompareCondition;
3667  ccmp_base_index += kNumCcmpOperands;
3668  DCHECK_LT(ccmp_base_index, instr->InputCount() - 1);
3669 
3670  InstructionCode code = static_cast<InstructionCode>(
3671  i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(opcode_index)).ToInt64());
3672 
3673  FlagsCondition default_condition = static_cast<FlagsCondition>(
3674  i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(default_condition_index)).ToInt64());
3675 
3676  StatusFlags default_flags =
3677  ConditionToDefaultFlags(FlagsConditionToCondition(default_condition));
3678 
3679  FlagsCondition compare_condition = static_cast<FlagsCondition>(
3680  i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(compare_condition_index)).ToInt64());
3681 
3682  if (code == kArm64Cmp) {
3683  gen->masm()->Ccmp(i.InputRegister64(compare_lhs_index),
3684  i.InputOperand64(compare_rhs_index), default_flags,
3685  FlagsConditionToCondition(compare_condition));
3686  } else if (code == kArm64Cmp32) {
3687  gen->masm()->Ccmp(i.InputRegister32(compare_lhs_index),
3688  i.InputOperand32(compare_rhs_index), default_flags,
3689  FlagsConditionToCondition(compare_condition));
3690  } else if (code == kArm64Float64Cmp) {
3691  gen->masm()->Fccmp(i.InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(compare_lhs_index),
3692  i.InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(compare_rhs_index),
3693  default_flags,
3694  FlagsConditionToCondition(compare_condition));
3695  } else {
3696  DCHECK_EQ(code, kArm64Float32Cmp);
3697  gen->masm()->Fccmp(i.InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(compare_lhs_index),
3698  i.InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(compare_rhs_index),
3699  default_flags,
3700  FlagsConditionToCondition(compare_condition));
3701  }
3702  }
3703 }

3705 // Assemble a conditional compare and boolean materializations after this
3706 // instruction.
3707 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchConditionalBoolean(Instruction* instr) {
3708  // Materialize a full 64-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3709  // last output of the instruction.
3710  DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3711  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3712  Register reg = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3713  DCHECK_GE(instr->InputCount(), 6);
3714 
3715  // Input ordering:
3716  // > InputCount - 1: number of ccmps.
3717  // > InputCount - 2: branch condition.
3718  size_t num_ccmps_index =
3719  instr->InputCount() - kConditionalSetEndOffsetOfNumCcmps;
3720  size_t set_condition_index =
3721  instr->InputCount() - kConditionalSetEndOffsetOfCondition;
3722  int64_t num_ccmps = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(num_ccmps_index)).ToInt64();
3723  size_t ccmp_base_index = set_condition_index - kNumCcmpOperands * num_ccmps;
3724  AssembleConditionalCompareChain(instr, num_ccmps, ccmp_base_index, this);
3725 
3726  FlagsCondition set_condition = static_cast<FlagsCondition>(
3727  i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(set_condition_index)).ToInt64());
3728  __ Cset(reg, FlagsConditionToCondition(set_condition));
3729 }

3731 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchConditionalBranch(Instruction* instr,
3732  BranchInfo* branch) {
3733  DCHECK_GE(instr->InputCount(), 6);
3734  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3735  // Input ordering:
3736  // > InputCount - 1: false block.
3737  // > InputCount - 2: true block.
3738  // > InputCount - 3: number of ccmps.
3739  // > InputCount - 4: branch condition.
3740  size_t num_ccmps_index =
3741  instr->InputCount() - kConditionalBranchEndOffsetOfNumCcmps;
3742  int64_t num_ccmps = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(num_ccmps_index)).ToInt64();
3743  size_t ccmp_base_index = instr->InputCount() -
3744  kConditionalBranchEndOffsetOfCondition -
3745  kNumCcmpOperands * num_ccmps;
3746  AssembleConditionalCompareChain(instr, num_ccmps, ccmp_base_index, this);
3747  Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(branch->condition);
3748  __ B(cc, branch->true_label);
3749  if (!branch->fallthru) __ B(branch->false_label);
3750 }

3752 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchSelect(Instruction* instr,
3753  FlagsCondition condition) {
3754  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3755  // The result register is always the last output of the instruction.
3756  size_t output_index = instr->OutputCount() - 1;
3757  MachineRepresentation rep =
3758  LocationOperand::cast(instr->OutputAt(output_index))->representation();
3759  Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3760  // We don't now how many inputs were consumed by the condition, so we have to
3761  // calculate the indices of the last two inputs.
3762  DCHECK_GE(instr->InputCount(), 2);
3763  size_t true_value_index = instr->InputCount() - 2;
3764  size_t false_value_index = instr->InputCount() - 1;
3765  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
3766  __ Fcsel(i.OutputFloat32Register(output_index),
3767  i.InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(true_value_index),
3768  i.InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(false_value_index), cc);
3769  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3770  __ Fcsel(i.OutputFloat64Register(output_index),
3771  i.InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(true_value_index),
3772  i.InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(false_value_index), cc);
3773  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
3774  __ Csel(i.OutputRegister32(output_index),
3775  i.InputOrZeroRegister32(true_value_index),
3776  i.InputOrZeroRegister32(false_value_index), cc);
3777  } else {
3778  DCHECK_EQ(rep, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3779  __ Csel(i.OutputRegister64(output_index),
3780  i.InputOrZeroRegister64(true_value_index),
3781  i.InputOrZeroRegister64(false_value_index), cc);
3782  }
3783 }

3785 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitch(Instruction* instr) {

3790  cases.push_back({i.InputInt32(index + 0), GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 1))});

3792  AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitchRange(input, i.InputRpo(1), cases.data(),
3793  cases.data() + cases.size());

3796 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchTableSwitch(Instruction* instr) {
3797  Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3798  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
3799  Register input = i.InputRegister64(0);
3800  size_t const case_count = instr->InputCount() - 2;
3801 
3802  base::Vector<Label*> cases = zone()->AllocateVector<Label*>(case_count);
3803  for (size_t index = 0; index < case_count; ++index) {
3804  cases[index] = GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 2));
3805  }
3806  Label* fallthrough = GetLabel(i.InputRpo(1));
3807  __ Cmp(input, Immediate(case_count));
3808  __ B(fallthrough, hs);
3809 
3810  Label* const jump_table = AddJumpTable(cases);
3811  Register addr = scope.AcquireX();
3812  __ Adr(addr, jump_table, MacroAssembler::kAdrFar);
3813  Register offset = scope.AcquireX();
3814  // Load the 32-bit offset.
3815  __ Ldrsw(offset, MemOperand(addr, input, LSL, 2));
3816  // The offset is relative to the address of 'jump_table', so add 'offset'
3817  // to 'addr' to reconstruct the absolute address.
3818  __ Add(addr, addr, offset);
3819  __ Br(addr);
3820 }

3854 void CodeGenerator::AssembleConstructFrame() {
3855  auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3856  __ AssertSpAligned();
3857 
3858  // The frame has been previously padded in CodeGenerator::FinishFrame().
3859  DCHECK_EQ(frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() % 2, 0);
3860  int required_slots =
3861  frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - frame()->GetFixedSlotCount();
3862 
3863  CPURegList saves =
3864  CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters());
3865  DCHECK_EQ(saves.Count() % 2, 0);
3866  CPURegList saves_fp =
3867  CPURegList(kDRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters());
3868  DCHECK_EQ(saves_fp.Count() % 2, 0);
3869  // The number of return slots should be even after aligning the Frame.
3870  const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3871  DCHECK_EQ(returns % 2, 0);
3872 
3873  if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3874  // Link the frame
3875  if (call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall()) {
3876  static_assert(StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize % 16 == 8);
3877  DCHECK_EQ(required_slots % 2, 1);
3878  __ Prologue();
3879  // Update required_slots count since we have just claimed one extra slot.
3880  static_assert(MacroAssembler::kExtraSlotClaimedByPrologue == 1);
3881  required_slots -= MacroAssembler::kExtraSlotClaimedByPrologue;
3882 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3883  } else if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() ||
3884  call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction() ||
3885  call_descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
3886  (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall() &&
3887  info()->GetOutputStackFrameType() ==
3888  StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY)) {
3889  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3890  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3891  __ Mov(scratch,
3892  StackFrame::TypeToMarker(info()->GetOutputStackFrameType()));
3893  __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, fp, scratch,
3894  kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3895  static constexpr int kSPToFPDelta = 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
3896  __ Add(fp, sp, kSPToFPDelta);
3897  if (call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
3898  // The C-API function has one extra slot for the PC.
3899  required_slots++;
3900  }
3901 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3902  } else if (call_descriptor->kind() == CallDescriptor::kCallCodeObject) {
3903  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3904  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3905  __ Mov(scratch,
3906  StackFrame::TypeToMarker(info()->GetOutputStackFrameType()));
3907  __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, fp, scratch, padreg);
3908  static constexpr int kSPToFPDelta = 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
3909  __ Add(fp, sp, kSPToFPDelta);
3910  // One of the extra slots has just been claimed when pushing the padreg.
3911  // We also know that we have at least one slot to claim here, as the typed
3912  // frame has an odd number of fixed slots, and all other parts of the
3913  // total frame slots are even, leaving {required_slots} to be odd.
3914  DCHECK_GE(required_slots, 1);
3915  required_slots--;
3916  } else {
3917  __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, fp);
3918  __ Mov(fp, sp);
3919  }
3920  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkFrameConstructed(__ pc_offset());
3921 
3922  // Create OSR entry if applicable
3923  if (info()->is_osr()) {
3924  // TurboFan OSR-compiled functions cannot be entered directly.
3925  __ Abort(AbortReason::kShouldNotDirectlyEnterOsrFunction);
3926 
3927  // Unoptimized code jumps directly to this entrypoint while the
3928  // unoptimized frame is still on the stack. Optimized code uses OSR values
3929  // directly from the unoptimized frame. Thus, all that needs to be done is
3930  // to allocate the remaining stack slots.
3931  __ RecordComment("-- OSR entrypoint --");
3932  osr_pc_offset_ = __ pc_offset();
3933  __ CodeEntry();
3934  size_t unoptimized_frame_slots = osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots();
3935 
3936 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL
3937  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3938  uint32_t expected_frame_size =
3939  static_cast<uint32_t>(osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots()) *
3940  kSystemPointerSize +
3941  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
3942  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3943  __ Add(scratch, sp, expected_frame_size);
3944  __ Cmp(scratch, fp);
3945  __ SbxCheck(eq, AbortReason::kOsrUnexpectedStackSize);
3946 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL
3947 
3948  DCHECK(call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall());
3949  DCHECK_EQ(unoptimized_frame_slots % 2, 1);
3950  // One unoptimized frame slot has already been claimed when the actual
3951  // arguments count was pushed.
3952  required_slots -=
3953  unoptimized_frame_slots - MacroAssembler::kExtraSlotClaimedByPrologue;
3954  }
3955 
3956 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3957  if (info()->IsWasm() && required_slots * kSystemPointerSize > 4 * KB) {
3958  // For WebAssembly functions with big frames we have to do the stack
3959  // overflow check before we construct the frame. Otherwise we may not
3960  // have enough space on the stack to call the runtime for the stack
3961  // overflow.
3962  Label done;
3963  // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
3964  // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
3965  // check in the condition code.
3966  if (required_slots * kSystemPointerSize < v8_flags.stack_size * KB) {
3967  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3968  Register stack_limit = temps.AcquireX();
3969  __ LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
3970  __ Add(stack_limit, stack_limit, required_slots * kSystemPointerSize);
3971  __ Cmp(sp, stack_limit);
3972  __ B(hs, &done);
3973  }
3974 
3975  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
3976  CPURegList regs_to_save(kXRegSizeInBits, RegList{});
3977  regs_to_save.Combine(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
3978  regs_to_save.Combine(
3979  WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
3980  for (auto reg : wasm::kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
3981  __ PushCPURegList(regs_to_save);
3982  CPURegList fp_regs_to_save(kDRegSizeInBits, DoubleRegList{});
3983  for (auto reg : wasm::kFpParamRegisters) fp_regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
3984  __ PushCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
3985  __ Mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(),
3986  required_slots * kSystemPointerSize);
3987  __ Add(
3988  WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
3989  Operand(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount() * kSystemPointerSize +
3990  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
3991  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
3992  __ PopCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
3993  __ PopCPURegList(regs_to_save);
3994  } else {
3995  __ Call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
3996  RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
3997  // The call does not return, hence we can ignore any references and just
3998  // define an empty safepoint.
3999  ReferenceMap* reference_map = zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(zone());
4000  RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
4001  if (v8_flags.debug_code) __ Brk(0);
4002  }
4003  __ Bind(&done);
4004  }
4005 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4006 
4007  // Skip callee-saved slots, which are pushed below.
4008  required_slots -= saves.Count();
4009  required_slots -= saves_fp.Count();
4010  required_slots -= returns;
4011 
4012  __ Claim(required_slots);
4013  }
4014 
4015  // Save FP registers.
4016  DCHECK_IMPLIES(saves_fp.Count() != 0,
4017  saves_fp.bits() == CPURegList::GetCalleeSavedV().bits());
4018  __ PushCPURegList(saves_fp);
4019 
4020  // Save registers.
4021  __ PushCPURegList(saves);
4022 
4023  if (returns != 0) {
4024  __ Claim(returns);
4025  }
4026 
4027  for (int spill_slot : frame()->tagged_slots()) {
4028  FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(spill_slot);
4029  DCHECK(offset.from_frame_pointer());
4030  __ Str(xzr, MemOperand(fp, offset.offset()));
4031  }
4032 }

4034 void CodeGenerator::AssembleReturn(InstructionOperand* additional_pop_count) {
4035  auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
4036 
4037  const int returns = RoundUp(frame()->GetReturnSlotCount(), 2);
4038  if (returns != 0) {
4039  __ Drop(returns);
4040  }
4041 
4042  // Restore registers.
4043  CPURegList saves =
4044  CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters());
4045  __ PopCPURegList(saves);
4046 
4047  // Restore fp registers.
4048  CPURegList saves_fp =
4049  CPURegList(kDRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters());
4050  __ PopCPURegList(saves_fp);
4051 
4052  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
4053 
4054  const int parameter_slots =
4055  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount());
4056  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4057 
4058  // {aditional_pop_count} is only greater than zero if {parameter_slots = 0}.
4059  // Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
4060  if (parameter_slots != 0) {
4061  if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
4062  DCHECK_EQ(g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32(), 0);
4063  } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4064  __ cmp(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count), Operand(0));
4065  __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedAdditionalPopValue);
4066  }
4067  }
4068 
4069 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4070  if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() &&
4071  v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
4072  {
4073  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{masm()};
4074  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
4075  __ Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
4076  __ Cmp(scratch,
4077  Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
4078  }
4079  Label done;
4080  __ B(ne, &done);
4081  CPURegList regs_to_save(kXRegSizeInBits, RegList{});
4082  for (auto reg : wasm::kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
4083  __ PushCPURegList(regs_to_save);
4084  CPURegList fp_regs_to_save(kDRegSizeInBits, DoubleRegList{});
4085  for (auto reg : wasm::kFpReturnRegisters) fp_regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
4086  __ PushCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
4087  __ Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
4088  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
4089  __ Mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
4090  __ PopCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
4091  __ PopCPURegList(regs_to_save);
4092  if (masm()->options().enable_simulator_code) {
4093  // The next instruction after shrinking stack is leaving the frame.
4094  // So SP will be set to old FP there. Switch simulator stack limit here.
4095  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{masm()};
4096  temps.Exclude(x16);
4097  __ LoadStackLimit(x16, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
4098  __ hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
4099  }
4100  __ bind(&done);
4101  }
4102 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4103 
4104  Register argc_reg = x3;
4105  // Functions with JS linkage have at least one parameter (the receiver).
4106  // If {parameter_slots} == 0, it means it is a builtin with
4107  // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel, which takes care of JS arguments popping
4108  // itself.
4109  const bool drop_jsargs = parameter_slots != 0 &&
4110  frame_access_state()->has_frame() &&
4111  call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall();
4112  if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
4113  AssembleDeconstructFrame();
4114  } else if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
4115  // Canonicalize JSFunction return sites for now unless they have an variable
4116  // number of stack slot pops.
4117  if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate() &&
4118  g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32() == 0) {
4119  if (return_label_.is_bound()) {
4120  __ B(&return_label_);
4121  return;
4122  } else {
4123  __ Bind(&return_label_);
4124  }
4125  }
4126  if (drop_jsargs) {
4127  // Get the actual argument count.
4128  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
4129  __ Ldr(argc_reg, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
4130  }
4131  AssembleDeconstructFrame();
4132  }
4133 
4134  if (drop_jsargs) {
4135  // We must pop all arguments from the stack (including the receiver). This
4136  // number of arguments is given by max(1 + argc_reg, parameter_slots).
4137  Label argc_reg_has_final_count;
4138  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
4139  if (parameter_slots > 1) {
4140  __ Cmp(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
4141  __ B(&argc_reg_has_final_count, ge);
4142  __ Mov(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
4143  __ Bind(&argc_reg_has_final_count);
4144  }
4145  __ DropArguments(argc_reg);
4146  } else if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
4147  int additional_count = g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32();
4148  __ DropArguments(parameter_slots + additional_count);
4149  } else if (parameter_slots == 0) {
4150  __ DropArguments(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count));
4151  } else {
4152  // {additional_pop_count} is guaranteed to be zero if {parameter_slots !=
4153  // 0}. Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
4154  __ DropArguments(parameter_slots);
4155  }
4156  __ AssertSpAligned();
4157  __ Ret();
4158 }

4162 void CodeGenerator::PrepareForDeoptimizationExits(
4163  ZoneDeque<DeoptimizationExit*>* exits) {
4164  __ ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
4165  // We are conservative here, reserving sufficient space for the largest deopt
4166  // kind.
4167  DCHECK_GE(Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize, Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
4168  __ CheckVeneerPool(
4169  false, false,
4170  static_cast<int>(exits->size()) * Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize);
4171 
4172  // Check which deopt kinds exist in this InstructionStream object, to avoid
4173  // emitting jumps to unused entries.
4174  bool saw_deopt_kind[kDeoptimizeKindCount] = {false};
4175  for (auto exit : *exits) {
4176  saw_deopt_kind[static_cast<int>(exit->kind())] = true;
4177  }
4178 
4179  // Emit the jumps to deoptimization entries.
4180  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4181  Register scratch = scope.AcquireX();
4182  static_assert(static_cast<int>(kFirstDeoptimizeKind) == 0);
4183  for (int i = 0; i < kDeoptimizeKindCount; i++) {
4184  if (!saw_deopt_kind[i]) continue;
4185  DeoptimizeKind kind = static_cast<DeoptimizeKind>(i);
4186  __ bind(&jump_deoptimization_entry_labels_[i]);
4187  __ LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Deoptimizer::GetDeoptimizationEntry(kind), scratch);
4188  __ Jump(scratch);
4189  }
4190 }

4192 AllocatedOperand CodeGenerator::Push(InstructionOperand* source) {
4193  auto rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4194  int new_slots = RoundUp<2>(ElementSizeInPointers(rep));
4195  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4196  int last_frame_slot_id =
4197  frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
4198  int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
4199  int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta + new_slots;
4200  AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
4201  if (source->IsRegister()) {
4202  __ Push(padreg, g.ToRegister(source));
4203  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4204  } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4205  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4206  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
4207  __ Ldr(scratch, g.ToMemOperand(source, masm()));
4208  __ Push(padreg, scratch);
4209  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4210  } else {
4211  // No push instruction for this operand type. Bump the stack pointer and
4212  // assemble the move.
4213  __ Sub(sp, sp, Operand(new_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4214  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4215  AssembleMove(source, &stack_slot);
4216  }
4217  temp_slots_ += new_slots;
4218  return stack_slot;
4219 }

4221 void CodeGenerator::Pop(InstructionOperand* dest, MachineRepresentation rep) {
4222  int dropped_slots = RoundUp<2>(ElementSizeInPointers(rep));
4223  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4224  if (dest->IsRegister()) {
4225  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4226  __ Pop(g.ToRegister(dest), padreg);
4227  } else if (dest->IsStackSlot()) {
4228  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4229  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4230  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
4231  __ Pop(scratch, padreg);
4232  __ Str(scratch, g.ToMemOperand(dest, masm()));
4233  } else {
4234  int last_frame_slot_id =
4235  frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
4236  int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
4237  int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta;
4238  AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
4239  AssembleMove(&stack_slot, dest);
4240  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4241  __ Add(sp, sp, Operand(dropped_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4242  }
4243  temp_slots_ -= dropped_slots;
4244 }

4254 void CodeGenerator::MoveToTempLocation(InstructionOperand* source,
4255  MachineRepresentation rep) {
4256  // Must be kept in sync with {MoveTempLocationTo}.
4257  DCHECK(!source->IsImmediate());
4258  move_cycle_.temps.emplace(masm());
4259  auto& temps = *move_cycle_.temps;
4260  // Temporarily exclude the reserved scratch registers while we pick one to
4261  // resolve the move cycle. Re-include them immediately afterwards as they
4262  // might be needed for the move to the temp location.
4263  temps.Exclude(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_regs));
4264  temps.ExcludeFP(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_fp_regs));
4265  if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep)) {
4266  if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
4267  Register scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireX();
4268  move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4269  } else if (temps.CanAcquireFP()) {
4270  // Try to use an FP register if no GP register is available for non-FP
4271  // moves.
4272  DoubleRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireD();
4273  move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4274  }
4275  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
4276  VRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireS();
4277  move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4278  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
4279  VRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireD();
4280  move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4281  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4282  VRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireQ();
4283  move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4284  }
4285  temps.Include(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_regs));
4286  temps.IncludeFP(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_fp_regs));
4287  if (move_cycle_.scratch_reg.has_value()) {
4288  // A scratch register is available for this rep.
4289  auto& scratch_reg = *move_cycle_.scratch_reg;
4290  if (scratch_reg.IsD() && !IsFloatingPoint(rep)) {
4291  AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER,
4292  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
4293  scratch_reg.code());
4294  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4295  if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4296  __ Ldr(g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch), g.ToMemOperand(source, masm()));
4297  } else {
4298  DCHECK(source->IsRegister());
4299  __ fmov(g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch), g.ToRegister(source));
4300  }
4301  } else {
4302  AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep,
4303  move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4304  AssembleMove(source, &scratch);
4305  }
4306  } else {
4307  // The scratch registers are blocked by pending moves. Use the stack
4308  // instead.
4309  Push(source);
4310  }
4311 }

4313 void CodeGenerator::MoveTempLocationTo(InstructionOperand* dest,
4314  MachineRepresentation rep) {
4315  if (move_cycle_.scratch_reg.has_value()) {
4316  auto& scratch_reg = *move_cycle_.scratch_reg;
4317  if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep) && scratch_reg.IsD()) {
4318  // We used a D register to move a non-FP operand, change the
4319  // representation to correctly interpret the InstructionOperand's code.
4320  AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER,
4321  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
4322  move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4323  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4324  if (dest->IsStackSlot()) {
4325  __ Str(g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch), g.ToMemOperand(dest, masm()));
4326  } else {
4327  DCHECK(dest->IsRegister());
4328  __ fmov(g.ToRegister(dest), g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch));
4329  }
4330  } else {
4331  AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep,
4332  move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4333  AssembleMove(&scratch, dest);
4334  }
4335  } else {
4336  Pop(dest, rep);
4337  }
4338  // Restore the default state to release the {UseScratchRegisterScope} and to
4339  // prepare for the next cycle.
4340  move_cycle_ = MoveCycleState();

4343 void CodeGenerator::SetPendingMove(MoveOperands* move) {
4344  auto move_type = MoveType::InferMove(&move->source(), &move->destination());
4345  if (move_type == MoveType::kStackToStack) {
4346  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4347  MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(&move->source(), masm());
4348  MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(&move->destination(), masm());
4349  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4350  if (move->source().IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
4351  VRegister temp = temps.AcquireQ();
4352  move_cycle_.scratch_fp_regs.set(temp);
4353  } else {
4354  Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
4355  move_cycle_.scratch_regs.set(temp);
4356  }
4357  int64_t src_offset = src.offset();
4358  unsigned src_size_log2 = CalcLSDataSizeLog2(LDR_x);
4359  int64_t dst_offset = dst.offset();
4360  unsigned dst_size_log2 = CalcLSDataSizeLog2(STR_x);
4361  // Offset doesn't fit into the immediate field so the assembler will emit
4362  // two instructions and use a second temp register.
4363  if ((src.IsImmediateOffset() &&
4364  !masm()->IsImmLSScaled(src_offset, src_size_log2) &&
4365  !masm()->IsImmLSUnscaled(src_offset)) ||
4366  (dst.IsImmediateOffset() &&
4367  !masm()->IsImmLSScaled(dst_offset, dst_size_log2) &&
4368  !masm()->IsImmLSUnscaled(dst_offset))) {
4369  Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
4370  move_cycle_.scratch_regs.set(temp);
4371  }
4372  }

4375 void CodeGenerator::AssembleMove(InstructionOperand* source,
4376  InstructionOperand* destination) {
4377  Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4378  // Helper function to write the given constant to the dst register.
4379  auto MoveConstantToRegister = [&](Register dst, Constant src) {
4380  if (src.type() == Constant::kHeapObject) {
4381  Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
4382  RootIndex index;
4383  if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
4384  __ LoadRoot(dst, index);
4385  } else {
4386  __ Mov(dst, src_object);
4387  }
4388  } else if (src.type() == Constant::kCompressedHeapObject) {
4389  Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
4390  RootIndex index;
4391  if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
4392  __ LoadTaggedRoot(dst, index);
4393  } else {
4394  // TODO(v8:8977): Even though this mov happens on 32 bits (Note the
4395  // .W()) and we are passing along the RelocInfo, we still haven't made
4396  // the address embedded in the code-stream actually be compressed.
4397  __ Mov(dst.W(),
4398  Immediate(src_object, RelocInfo::COMPRESSED_EMBEDDED_OBJECT));
4399  }
4400  } else if (src.type() == Constant::kExternalReference) {
4401  __ Mov(dst, src.ToExternalReference());
4402  } else {
4403  Operand src_op = g.ToImmediate(source);
4404  if (src.type() == Constant::kInt32 && src_op.NeedsRelocation(masm())) {
4405  // Use 32-bit loads for relocatable 32-bit constants.
4406  dst = dst.W();
4407  }
4408  __ Mov(dst, src_op);
4409  }
4410  };
4411  switch (MoveType::InferMove(source, destination)) {
4412  case MoveType::kRegisterToRegister:
4413  if (source->IsRegister()) {
4414  __ Mov(g.ToRegister(destination), g.ToRegister(source));
4415  } else {
4416  DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register() || source->IsFloatRegister() ||
4417  source->IsDoubleRegister());
4418  __ Mov(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination).Q(),
4419  g.ToDoubleRegister(source).Q());
4420  }
4421  return;
4422  case MoveType::kRegisterToStack: {
4423  MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4424  if (source->IsRegister()) {
4425  __ Str(g.ToRegister(source), dst);
4426  } else {
4427  VRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
4428  if (source->IsFloatRegister() || source->IsDoubleRegister()) {
4429  __ Str(src, dst);
4430  } else {
4431  DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register());
4432  __ Str(src.Q(), dst);
4433  }
4434  }
4435  return;
4436  }
4437  case MoveType::kStackToRegister: {
4438  MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source, masm());
4439  if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4440  __ Ldr(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4441  } else {
4442  VRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4443  if (destination->IsFloatRegister() || destination->IsDoubleRegister()) {
4444  __ Ldr(dst, src);
4445  } else {
4446  DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128Register());
4447  __ Ldr(dst.Q(), src);
4448  }
4449  }
4450  return;
4451  }
4452  case MoveType::kStackToStack: {
4453  MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source, masm());
4454  MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4455  if (source->IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
4456  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4457  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireQ();
4458  __ Ldr(temp, src);
4459  __ Str(temp, dst);
4460  } else {
4461  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4462  Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
4463  __ Ldr(temp, src);
4464  __ Str(temp, dst);
4465  }
4466  return;
4467  }
4468  case MoveType::kConstantToRegister: {
4469  Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
4470  if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4471  MoveConstantToRegister(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4472  } else {
4473  VRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4474  if (destination->IsFloatRegister()) {
4475  __ Fmov(dst.S(), src.ToFloat32());
4476  } else {
4477  DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleRegister());
4478  __ Fmov(dst, src.ToFloat64().value());
4479  }
4480  }
4481  return;
4482  }
4483  case MoveType::kConstantToStack: {
4484  Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
4485  MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4486  if (destination->IsStackSlot()) {
4487  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4488  Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
4489  MoveConstantToRegister(temp, src);
4490  __ Str(temp, dst);
4491  } else if (destination->IsFloatStackSlot()) {
4492  if (base::bit_cast<int32_t>(src.ToFloat32()) == 0) {
4493  __ Str(wzr, dst);
4494  } else {
4495  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4496  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireS();
4497  __ Fmov(temp, src.ToFloat32());
4498  __ Str(temp, dst);
4499  }
4500  } else {
4501  DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleStackSlot());
4502  if (src.ToFloat64().AsUint64() == 0) {
4503  __ Str(xzr, dst);
4504  } else {
4505  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4506  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireD();
4507  __ Fmov(temp, src.ToFloat64().value());
4508  __ Str(temp, dst);
4509  }
4510  }
4511  return;
4512  }
4513  }
4514  UNREACHABLE();
4515 }

4517 void CodeGenerator::AssembleSwap(InstructionOperand* source,
4518  InstructionOperand* destination) {

4520  switch (MoveType::InferSwap(source, destination)) {

4529  } else {
4530  DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register());

4533  }
4534  return;

4538  if (source->IsRegister()) {
4539  Register temp = scope.AcquireX();

4571  __ Str(temp_0.Q(), dst);

4575  __ Ldr(temp_1, dst);
